# AWS Resources Naming Convention

Standard naming convention for AWS resources to ensure consistent identification.

## Naming Structure

### Multi-VPC Solutions
```
<object-type>-<vpc-name>-<object-name>[-<version>]
```
Examples: `i-mgmt-bastion-linux-v01`, `net-dev-private-az1`, `sgr-prod-web-servers`

### Single VPC Solutions
```
<object-type>-<object-name>[-<version>]
```
Examples: `i-bastion-linux-v01`, `alb-web-frontend`

## Format Rules

- **All lowercase letters**
- **No spaces** - use hyphens (`-`) as separators
- **Version format**: `v##` (e.g., `v01`, `v02`) - never use `new`, `old`, `current`
- **Temporary objects**: Add `_temp` suffix

## Object Type Prefixes

| Prefix | Resource | Prefix | Resource |
|--------|----------|--------|----------|
| `i` | EC2 Instance | `vpc` | VPC |
| `lt` | Launch Template | `net` | Subnet |
| `asg` | Auto-Scaling Group | `sgr` | Security Group |
| `alb` | Application LB | `rtb` | Routing Table |
| `nlb` | Network LB | `igw` | Internet Gateway |
| `tg` | Target Group | `nat` | NAT Gateway |
| `ecs` | ECS Cluster | `vpce` | VPC Endpoint |
| `ecr` | ECR Repository | `eip` | Elastic IP |
| `svc` | ECS Service | `pcx` | Peering Connection |
| `taskdef` | ECS Task Definition | `acl` | Network ACL |
| `lambda` | Lambda Function | `policy` | IAM Policy |
| `rds` | RDS Instance | `role` | IAM Role |
| `cb` | CodeBuild | `cmk` | KMS Key |
| `repo` | CodeCommit | `lgr` | CloudWatch Log Group |
| `cf` | CloudFormation Stack | `ebr` | EventBridge Rule |
| `apigw` | API Gateway | `sns` | SNS Topic |

## Environment Examples

### Development
```
vpc-dev
net-dev-private-az1
sgr-dev-web-servers
i-dev-app-server-v01
alb-dev-web-frontend
ecs-dev-cluster
```

### Production
```
vpc-prod
net-prod-private-az1
sgr-prod-db-access
rds-prod-primary-v02
lambda-prod-data-processor
```

## Required Tags

| Tag | Purpose | Example |
|-----|---------|---------|
| `Name` | Resource identifier | `i-dev-web-server-v01` |
| `Description` | Resource purpose | `Development web server` |
| `Created-by` | Creator identity | `john.doe@company.com` |
| `Environment` | Environment type | `dev`, `stg`, `prod` |
| `Project` | Project name | `ceel-poc` |

## AgentCore-Specific Naming

| Resource | Pattern | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| AgentCore Runtime | `<Project><Env><Agent>Runtime-*` | `CeelPocOrchestratorRuntime-xyz` |
| Backend ECR | `<project>-<agent>` | `ceel-orchestrator`, `ceel-analyzer` |
| Frontend ECR | `<project>-frontend` | `ceel-frontend` |
| Log Group (Agent) | `/aws/agentcore/<project>-<agent>` | `/aws/agentcore/ceel-orchestrator` |
| Log Group (ECS) | `/ecs/<project>-frontend` | `/ecs/ceel-frontend` |
| ALB | `alb-<project>-<env>` | `alb-ceel-poc` |
| ECS Cluster | `ecs-<project>-<env>-cluster` | `ecs-ceel-poc-cluster` |
| IAM Role (Agent) | `<project>-<env>-<agent>-role` | `ceel-poc-orchestrator-role` |
